Stereotype.name: annotation
Stereotype.notes: This is a plain annotation which does not have further formal data.

Stereotype.name: swbitrepresentation
Stereotype.notes: Description of the structure of a bit variable: Comprises of the bitPosition in a memory object (e.g. swHostVariable, which stands parallel to swBitRepresentation) and the numberOfBits . In this way, interrelated memory areas can be described. Non-related memory areas are not supported.

Stereotype.name: swdatadefprops
Stereotype.notes: This class is a collection of properties relevant for data objects under various aspects. One could consider this class as a "pattern of inheritance by aggregation". The properties can be applied to all objects of all classes in which SwDataDefProps is aggregated.

Tag.name: additionalNativeTypeQualifier
Tag.description: This attribute is used to declare native qualifiers of the programming language which can neither be deduced from the baseType (e.g. because the data object describes a pointer) nor from other more abstract attributes. Examples are qualifiers like "volatile", "strict" or "enum" of the C-language. All such declarations have to be put into one string.

Tag.name: annotation
Tag.description: This aggregation allows to add annotations (yellow pads...) related to the current data object.

Tag.name: baseType
Tag.description: Base type associated with the containing data object.

Tag.name: compuMethod
Tag.description: Computation method associated with the semantics of this data object.

Tag.name: dataContr
Tag.description: Data constraint for this data object.

Tag.name: displayFormat
Tag.description: This property describes how a number is to be rendered e.g. in documents or in a measurement and calibration system
